{"title_page": "Hetty Feather (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Short description|British television series}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hetty Feather\n| image                    = Hetty Feather Title Card.jpg\n| caption                  = Title Card\n| genre                    = [[Drama series|Drama]]\n| runtime                  = 28&nbsp;minutes\n| executive_producer       = Foz Allan (Series 1) <br />Alison Davis (Series 2-6)\n| producer                 = David Collier\n| company                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]]\n| writer                   = [[Helen Blakeman]]\n| director                 = {{plainlist|\n* [[Chloe Thomas]] \n* Paul Walker \n* Delyth Thomas\n* Reza Moradi\n}}\n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n*Isabel Clifton\n*Dasharn Anderson\n*Polly Allen\n*[[Eva Pope]]\n*Gus Barry\n*Ava Merson-O'Brien\n*[[Eleanor Worthington Cox]]\n*[[Fern Deacon]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Andy Price]]\n| composer                 = [[Andy Price]]\n| country                  = United Kingdom\n| language                 = English\n| network                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]] <br> [[CBBC HD]] <br> [[CITV]] (6.00am)\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2015|5|11|df=y}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| num_series               = 6\n| num_episodes             = 55\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| picture_format           = [[576i]]\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/shows/hetty-feather\n}}\n\n'''Hetty Feather''' is a British [[Children's television series|children's]] [[drama]] series, which focuses on the life of the title character who was abandoned as a baby and lives in a [[Foundling Hospital]] in London. It is based on the [[Hetty Feather|book of the same name]] by [[Jacqueline Wilson]]. The first series aired from 11 May 2015 to 6 July 2015. The series began airing in the United States on [[BYUtv]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=Sarah Harris for the [[Daily Herald (Utah)|Daily Herald]] |url=https://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/television/byutv-spring-programming-adds-downton-abbey-for-kids-studio-c/article_e1e45d86-4650-51a4-9620-552527a6ca56.html|title=BYUtv spring programming adds 'Downton Abbey' for kids, 'Studio C' game show spinoff}}</ref> Cast member [[Fern Deacon]] confirmed that the sixth series, accompanied by a feature-length special, would be the final series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-nD19ZhImd/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link|title=Thank you for a wonderful 4 years with the brilliant Hetty Feather cast and crew. The Chronicles of Hetty Feather starts on iplayer on the 6th April followed by the final series on the 10th April and airs on @cbbc on the 13th April at 7pm \ud83d\udc9a #hettyfeather #cbbc #finale #lastseries|date=5 April 2020|last=Deacon|first=Fern|access-date=6 April 2020|work=[[Instagram]]}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nThe premise of the series revolves around Hetty Feather, who was abandoned as a baby. She was fostered by Peg with Gideon Smeed, her foster brother and when they turned 5, they had to return to the [[Foundling Hospital]]. The series is set during 1887 and filmed at [[Cobham Hall]], [[Cobham, Kent]] and [[The Maidstone Studios]] as their production base.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kent Film Office|url=http://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/2015/04/hetty-feather-2015/|title=Kent Film Office Hetty Feather Article}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://screenterrier.blogspot.co.uk/2015/04/first-look-at-hetty-feather.html|work=Screen Terrier|title=First look at Hetty Feather|date=2015-04-04|accessdate=2015-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2015/19/hetty-feather|work=BBC Media Centre|title=Hetty Feather|date=2015|accessdate=2015-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Kent Film Office|url=http://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/2016/05/hetty-feather-series-2-2016/|title=Kent Film Office Hetty Feather Series 2 Article}}</ref> During series 3, filming moved to Belmont House in Faversham, Kent.\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Main characters===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Character\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Actor\n! style=\"width:120px;\"| Duration\n! style=\"width:90px;\"| Series\n|-\n| Hetty Feather || Isabel Clifton || rowspan=\"2\"|1x01\u20136x03 || rowspan=\"4\"|Series 1\u20136\n|-\n| Gideon Smeed || Dasharn Anderson\n|-\n| Sheila Ormsby || Polly Allen || 1x01-5x01, 5x09-6x03\n|-\n| Matron Gertrude Bottomly || [[Eva Pope]] || 1x01\u20133x10, 4x04, 5x11-5x12, 6x02-6x03 \n|-\n| Harriet Summers || Ava Merson-O'Brien || rowspan=\"2\"|1x01\u20133x08, 6x01-6x03 || rowspan=\"8\"|Series 1-3, 6\n|- \n| Mathias Grigg || Gus Barry\n|-\n| Donald Cranbourne || [[Matthew Ashforde]] || rowspan=\"5\"|1x01-3x08, 6x02-6x03 \n|-\n| Walter Brittle || Aaron Niles\n|-\n| Ned || David Knight\n|-\n| Judd Mortimer || Joshua Langley\n|-\n| Nurse Macclesfield || Susan McArdle\n|-\n| Nurse Winterson/Mrs Clark || Rosalyn Wright || rowspan=\"1\"|1x01-3x08, 6x03\n|-\n|George Calendar || Mark Frost || 3x07, 3x09-4x10, 5x12-6x03 || rowspan=\"4\"|Series 3-6\n|-\n| Edwin Calendar || Hugo Cracknell || rowspan=3|3x09-6x03\n|-\n| Agnes ||[[Fern Deacon]]\n|-\n| Constance Calendar || Tabitha Byron\n|-\n| Lizzie || India Brown || rowspan\"1\"|4x03-6x03 || rowspan=\"2\"|Series 4-6\n|-\n| Lady Grenford ||  [[Georgie Glen]] || 4x01-4x10, 5x03-6x03 \n|-\n|}\n\n===Guest and recurring characters===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Character\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Actor\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| Duration\n! style=\"width:20px;\"| Series\n|-\n| Colonel Rupert Brigwell || [[Christopher Villiers]] || 1x01\u20133x08, 4x04|| Series 1\u20134\n|-\n| Arthur || Ewan Harris || rowspan=\"2\"|1x01\u20131x04 || rowspan=\"2\"|Series 1\n|-\n| Jack || Eliot Carrington\n|-\n| Young Hetty || Jocelyn MacNa