e = {{Start date|2019|12|12|df=y}}<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://twitter.com/MissIssyClifton/status/1203949150280310785?s=19 | title= Isabel Clifton on Twitter UK Christmas Special Date| date=2019-12-09}}</ref>\n| AltDate         = 8 December 2019<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.byutv.org/post/4032a776-1d85-4227-8237-0a396228a3a4/christmas-schedule-2019 | title= BYUtv Christmas Schedule 2018| date=2019-11-06}}</ref> \n| ShortSummary    = Hetty comes up with a plan to get Sheila reinstated for Christmas, but when the street gang steals the food meant for the poor at church everyone gets separated. In the end tons of problems arise which might make it where the gang can't make it home for Christmas. \n\n'''Note''': Matron Bottomly returns for this episode\n'''Absent''': William Calendar\n| LineColor       = 87CEEB\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 52\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = A Christmas Adventure: Part Two\n| DirectedBy      = Ian Barnes\n| WrittenBy       = Matt Evans\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|12|12|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 8 December 2019\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty is held captive by Matron Bottomly and the street gang, Gideon tries to figure out how to help Sheila escape the workhouse, and Rosamund and Lady Grenford are in prison for looking poor. Seeing no other choice Jack and Agnes begin searching the streets hoping to help everyone make it back to Calendar Hall. \n\n'''Note''': Matron Bottomly returns for this episode\n   \n'''Returned''': George Calendar \n'''Absent''': William Calendar\n| LineColor       = 87CEEB\n}}\n}}\n\n===Series 6 (2020)===\n{{Episode table |background=#B533FF |overall=6 |series=6 |title=21 |director=16 |writer=20 |airdate=16 |altdate=17 |airdateT=Original air date<br>(CBBC) |altdateT=Original air date<br>(BYUtv) |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 53\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = The Final Chapter: Part One\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = Robin Mukherjee\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|13|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = TBC\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty is sacked when George blames her for insulting Rosamund, who has died in childbirth. \n'''Last Appearance''': Rosamund Calendar\n| LineColor       = B533FF\n}}\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 54\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = The Final Chapter: Part Two\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = Matt Evans\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|14|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = TBC\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty meets Matron living on the streets, while Mathias' reunion with the gang threatens his wedding to Harriet. Meanwhile, George plans to send his children away and return to India. \n| LineColor       = B533FF\n}}\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 55\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = The Final Chapter: Part Three\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = Helen Blakeman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = TBC\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty saves Matron from a street gang and Constance runs away to find Hetty. Mathias swears his love for Harriet, while Hetty is forced to return to Calendar Hall before she can move on. \n| LineColor       = B533FF\n}}\n}}\n<!--Do not add the next season until a table can be created for it, per WP:TVUPCOMING and WP:TVOVERVIEW!-->\n\n==DVD releases==\nThe first series of Hetty Feather was released on DVD on 27 July 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbcshop.com/childrens/hetty-feather/invt/dazd0184|work=BBC Shop|title=Hetty Feather|date=2015|accessdate=2015-07-06}}</ref> The first season was given a U (Universal) and a PG rating by the BBFC for mild bad language, mild scenes of threat and peril, and mild adult themes (specifically scenes centred on death and bereavement). The second series of Hetty Feather was released on DVD on 18 July 2016.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Hetty-Feather-BBC-Jacqueline-Wilson/dp/B01ERW1TQU/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1464694496&sr=8-1&keywords=hetty+feather+series+2 | title=Hetty Feather Series 2| date=2016-07-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{BBC programme}}\n* {{IMDb title|4670954}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hetty Feather}}\n[[Category:2010s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:2020s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:2015 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020 British television series endings]]\n[[Category:British children's television programmes]]\n[[Category:BBC children's television programmes]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series set in the 19th century]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in London]]\n[[Category:Television series about orphans]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|British television series}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hetty Feather\n| image                    = Hetty Feather Title Card.jpg\n| caption                  = Title Card\n| genre                    = [[Drama series|Drama]]\n| runtime                  = 28&nbsp;minutes\n| executive_producer       = Foz Allan (Series 1) <br />Alison Davis (Series 2-6)\n| producer                 = David Collier\n| company                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]]\n| writer                   = [[Helen Blakeman]]\n| director                 = {{plainlist|\n* [[Chloe Thomas]] \n* Paul Walker \n* Delyth Thomas\n* Reza Moradi\n}}\n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n*Isabel Clifton\n*Dasharn Anderson\n*Polly Allen\n*[[Eva Pope]]\n*Gus Barry\n*Ava Merson-O'Brien\n*[[Eleanor Worthington Cox]]\n*[[Fern Deacon]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Andy Price]]\n| composer                 = [[Andy Price]]\n| country                  = United Kingdom\n| language                 = English\n| network                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]] <br> [[CBBC HD]] <br> [[CITV]] (6.00am)\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2015|5|11|df=y}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| num_series               = 6\n| num_episodes             = 55\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| picture_format           = [[576i]]\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/shows/hetty-feather\n}}\n\n'''Hetty Feather''' is a British [[Children's television series|children's]] [[drama]] series, which focuses on the life of the title character who was abandoned as a baby and lives in a [[Foundling Hospital]] in London. It is based on the [[Hetty Feather|book of the same name]] by [[Jacqueline Wilson]]. The first series aired from 11 May 2015 to 6 July 2015. The series began airing in the United States on [[BYUtv]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=Sarah Harris for the [[Daily Herald (Utah)|Daily Herald]] |url=https://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/television/byutv-spring-programming-adds-downton-abbey-for-kids-studio-c/article_e1e45d86-4650-51a4-9620-552527a6ca56.html|title=BYUtv spring programming adds 'Downton Abbey' for kids, 'Studio C' game show spinoff}}</ref> Cast member [[Fern Deacon]] confirmed that the sixth series, accompanied by a feature-length special, would be the final series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-nD19ZhImd/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link|title=Thank you for a wonderful 4 years with the brilliant Hetty Feather cast and crew. The Chronicles of Hetty Feather starts on iplayer on the 6th April followed by the final series on the 10th April and airs on @cbbc on the 13th April at 7pm \ud83d\udc9a #hettyfeather #cbbc #finale #lastseries|date=5 April 2020|last=Deacon|first=Fern|access-date=6 April 2020|work=[[Instagram]]}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nThe premise of the series revolves around Hetty Feather, who was abandoned as a baby. She was fostered by Peg with Gideon Smeed, her foster brother and when they turned 5, they had to return to the [[Foundling Hospital]]. The series is set during 1887 and filmed at [[Cobham Hall]], [[Cobham, Kent]] and [[The Maidstone Studios]] as their production base.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kent Film Office|url=http://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/2015/04/hetty-feather-2015/|title=Kent Film Office Hetty Feather Article}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://screenterrier.blogspot.co.uk/2015/04/first-look-at-hetty-feather.html|work=Screen Terrier|title=First look at Hetty Feather|date=2015-04-04|accessdate=2015-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2015/19/hetty-feather|work=BBC Media Centre|title=Hetty Feather|date=2015|accessdate=2015-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Kent Film Office|url=http://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/2016/05/hetty-feather-series-2-2016/|title=Kent Film Office Hetty Feather Series 2 Article}}</ref> During series 3, filming moved to Belmont House in Faversham, Kent.\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Main characters===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Character\n! style=\"width:140px;\"| Actor\n! style=\"width:120px;\"| Duration\n! style=\"width:90px;\"| Series\n|-\n| Hetty Feather || Isabel Clifton || rowspan=\"2\"|1x01\u20136x03 || rowspan=\"4\"|Series 1\u20136\n|-\n| Gideon Smeed || Dasharn Anderson\n|-\n| Sheila Ormsby || Polly Allen || 1x01-5x01, 5x09-6x03\n|-\n| Matron Gertrude Bottomly || [[Eva Pope]] || 1x01\u20133x10, 4x04, 5x11-5x12, 6x02-6x03 \n|-\n| Harriet Summers || Ava Merson-O'Brien || rowspan=\"2\"|1x01\u20133x08, 6x01-6x03 || rowspan=\"8\"|Series 1-3, 6\n|- \n| Mathias Grigg || Gus Barry\n|-\n| Donald Cranbourne || [[Matthew Ashforde]] || rowspan=\"5\"|1x01-3x08, 6x02-6x03 \n|-\n| Walter Brittle || Aaron Niles\n|-\n| Ned || David Knight\n|-\n| Judd Mortimer || Joshua Langley\n|-\n| Nurse Macclesfield || Susan McArdle\n|-\n| Nurse Winterson/Mrs Clark || Rosalyn Wright || rowspan=\"1\"|1x01-3x08, 6x03\n|-\n|George Calendar || Mark Frost || 3x07, 3x09-4x10, 5x12-6x03 || rowspan=\"4\"|Series 3-6\n|-\n| Edwin Calendar || Hugo Cracknell || rowspan