 children: Emily, Edwin and Constance.\n\n'''First Appearance''': Agnes, Jack, Emily Calendar, Edwin Calendar and Constance Calendar\n\n| LineColor       = 7A335D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = The Past Returns\n| DirectedBy      = Delyth Thomas\n| WrittenBy       = Helen Blakeman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|7|10|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 14 October 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty and Gideon try to rescue a kidnapped girl but comes face-to-face with Matron which ends with Matron going to prison. Hetty visits her Mum.\n\n'''Last Appearance''': Matron Bottomly\n\n'''Note''': Ida Battersea returns for this episode\n\n| LineColor       = 7A335D\n}}\n}}\n\n===Series 4 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |background=#FF5F5F |overall=5 |series=5 |title=21 |director=16 |writer=20 |airdate=16 |altdate=17 |airdateT=Original air date<br>(CBBC) |altdateT=Original air date<br>(BYUtv) |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = The New Arrival\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = Helen Blakeman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|7|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 21 October 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty discovers an explosive secret from Rosamund Calendar- she lost a baby years ago called Charles who she believes Matron may know of while Gideon fears he caused Edwin's life-threatening accident. Rosamund gives birth to another baby who she names William. New housekeeper Brodie arrives at Calendar Hall.\n\n'''First Appearance''': Lady Grenford, Mrs Brody, William Calendar and Mrs Whittock\n\n| LineColor       = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Trouble\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = [[Robin Mukherjee (writer)|Robin Mukherjee]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|15|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 21 October 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty is forced to cover when Rosamund goes missing on the day of William's christening, while Gideon and Jack find themselves in muddy trouble.\n| LineColor       = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Family\n| DirectedBy      = Reza Moradi\n| WrittenBy       = Victoria Asare-Archer\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|21|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 28 October 2018\n| ShortSummary    = A new arrival at the Hall threatens Agnes and Sheila's jobs while Gideon falls out with Emily. Sheila struggles looking after Constance.\n\n'''First Appearance''': Lizzie\n\n| LineColor       = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 34\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Prisons\n| DirectedBy      = Sallie Aprahamian\n| WrittenBy       = Joseph Lidster\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|28|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 28 October 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty steels herself to face her old enemy, while Lady Grenford introduces the family to her handsome young grandson, Robert.\n\n'''Note''': Matron Bottomly returns for this episode\n\n| LineColor       = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 35\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = For Shame\n| DirectedBy      = Sallie Aprahamian\n| WrittenBy       = Hilary Frankland\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|6|4|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 4 November 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Agnes's job is put at risk when her family secret is revealed, while Emily argues with her father about her future. Jack thinks Gideon has betrayed him.\n| LineColor       = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 36\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = Wolves\n| DirectedBy      = Sallie Aprahamian\n| WrittenBy       = Gareth Sergeant\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|6|11|df=y}}\n| AltDate         = 4 November 2018\n| ShortSummary    = Hetty and Gideon are shocked when a figure from their past turns up unexpectedly, while Lizzie is terrified by the story of a savage wolf boy on 